genresAdvancedInfo.name: vlaamse cabaret
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Vlaamse cabaret is a type of Belgian comedy that originated in the early 20th century. It is known for its satirical and often politically charged humor, with performers using their wit and humor to comment on current events and social issues. The performances are usually in Flemish, the Dutch dialect spoken in Belgium, and often involve music and singing. Vlaamse cabaret has a rich history in Belgian culture and continues to be a popular form of entertainment today.
